ugurates track; his little horse [of either sex; caressive diminutive; hence "naggy", which Miss Deutsch will find in Webster, unabridged, 1950, and elsewhere], snow having sensed [chuyat' applies to more senses than that of smell], shambles at trot any old way."

This Miss Deutsch renders as:

Here's winter ... The exultant peasant

Upon his sledge tries out the road;

His mare scents snow upon the pleasant

Keen air, and trots without a goad.

